'''Yassin Enzo Fortuné''' (born 30 January 1999) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for [[Liga Portugal 2]] club [[F.C. Vizela|Vizela]]. Born in France, he represents the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]].<ref name="Mattias">{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.us/arsenal/story/2799233/arsenal-teenager-yassin-fortune-signs-professional-contract |title=Arsenal teenager Yassin Fortune signs professional contract |editor=Mattias, Karen |date=2 February 2016 |publisher=ESPN |access-date=30 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Bordeaux-qui-sera-le-nouveau-thomas-toure/578351 |title=Le Français Yassin Fortune devient professionnel à Arsenal |editor=Press |date=3 February 2016 |publisher=Le Équipe |access-date=30 March 2016}} {{in lang|fr}}</ref>

==Early years==
Fortuné was born in Aubervilliers, France to a Haitian father and Algerian mother.<ref name="Fortuné Eligible">{{cite web|url=http://lagazettedufennec.com/filinfo/arsenal-yassin-fortune-passe-pro-chez-les-gunners/ |title=Arsenal : Yassin Fortune passe pro chez les Gunners |editor=Press |date=2 February 2016 |publisher=La Gazette du Fennec |access-date=30 March 2016}} {{in lang|fr}}</ref> As a child growing up in the [[Paris]] area, Fortuné idolized Arsenal star and fellow countryman [[Thierry Henry]], and has said he patterns his game after him,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.insidefutbol.com/2015/12/25/thierry-henry-my-idol-but-im-learning-from-danny-welbeck-arsenal-starlet/259914/|title=Thierry Henry My Idol, But I'm Learning From Danny Welbeck |editor=Press |date=25 December 2015|publisher=Inside Futbol|access-date=2 July 2016}}</ref> but compares himself to [[Danny Welbeck]].<ref name="Mattias"/>

Fortuné started his career with Stains FC in the Ligue de Paris Île-de-France de football<ref>[https://www.fff.fr/la-vie-des-clubs/24745/infos-cles FFF - Stains F.C.]</ref> in January 2008. He left the club the same year and joined the third-tier [[Red Star F.C.|Red Star]] in France in August.<ref name="Corless">{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/who-yassin-fortune-arsenal-beat-5721726 |title=Who is Yassin Fortune? Arsenal 'beat Manchester United to signing of Ligue 1 starlet' |editor=Corless, Liam |date=19 May 2015 |publisher=Mirror |access-date=2 July 2016}}</ref> In July 2012, Fortuné signed with [[RC Lens]]<ref name="Corless"/>

At age 16, Fortuné signed his first professional contract in July 2015 with [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] on a three-year £3 million deal,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/transfers/arsenal-beat-manchester-united-to-3million-lens-teenager-yassin-fortune-10259983.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220507/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/transfers/arsenal-beat-manchester-united-to-3million-lens-teenager-yassin-fortune-10259983.html |archive-date=7 May 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live|title=Arsenal 'beat' Manchester United to £3million Lens teenager Yassin Fortune|editor=Sheen, Tom|date=19 May 2015|publisher=Independent |access-date=2 July 2016}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2470006-arsenal-transfer-news-latest-wojciech-szczesny-yassin-fortune-rumours |title=Arsenal Transfer News: Latest Wojciech Szczesny, Yassin Fortune Rumours |editor=Verschueren, Gianni|date=19 May 2015 |publisher=Bleacher Report |access-date=2 July 2016}}</ref> with two years as a scholar and one year on professional terms<ref name="Corless"/><ref name="talkSport">{{cite web|url=http://talksport.com/football/arsenal-hand-professional-deal-17-year-old-french-forward-yassin-fortune-160202183557 |title=Arsenal hand professional deal to 17-year-old French forward Yassin Fortune |editor=Press |date=2 February 2016 |publisher=talkSport |access-date=2 July 2016}}</ref> after facing competition from [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.express.co.uk/sport/football/578087/Arsenal-Sign-Man-United-Target-Yassin-Fortune|title=Arsenal BEAT Man United to sign star French attacking midfielder|editor=Cambridge, James|date=18 May 2015|publisher=Express|access-date=2 July 2016}}</ref>

Though with the club for three years, Fortuné only made 22 appearances for the Arsenal U18, U19 and U23 sides, scoring just two goals and three assists after being marred by injuries.<ref name="Lee">{{cite web|url=http://dailycannon.com/2018/06/official-yassin-fortune-rejects-arsenal-deal-signs-for-fc-sion/|title=Official: Yassin Fortune rejects Arsenal deal, signs for FC Sion|editor=Hurley, Lee|date=15 June 2018|publisher=Daily Cannon|access-date=22 July 2018}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/match/report/1617/post/under-18/u-18s-fulham-3-2-arsenal-report|title=U-18s: Fulham 3-2 Arsenal - Report|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|date=6 February 2017|access-date=30 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181129202134/https://www.arsenal.com/match/report/1617/post/under-18/u-18s-fulham-3-2-arsenal-report|archive-date=29 November 2018|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite news|title=U18s: Arsenal 3-0 Manchester United – Willock nets brace to increase title hopes|url=http://dailycannon.com/2017/05/u18s-arsenal-3-0-manchester-united-willock-nets-brace-to-increase-title-hopes/|publisher=Daily Cannon|date=5 May 2017|access-date=30 November 2018}}</ref>

==Club career==
===FC Sion===
In May 2018, after three years of not making a professional appearance for the senior Arsenal club, Fortuné had rejected a new three-year contract offer to stay with the club and agreed to four-year deal with [[FC Sion]] of the Swiss first division with Arsenal agreeing to transfer, becoming his first professional club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tribalfootball.com/articles/fortune-and-reine-adelaide-to-quit-arsenal-after-wenger-departure-4234208 |title=Fortune and Reine-Adelaide to quit Arsenal after Wenger departure |editor=Paul, Vegas |date=2 June 2018 |publisher=Tribal Football |access-date=22 July 2018}}</ref><ref name="Lee"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://offsidefootball.com/arsenal-reach-agreement-over-french-centre-forwards-deal/ |title=Arsenal reach agreement over French centre-forward's deal |editor=Van De Laar, Timo |date=16 June 2018 |publisher=Offside Football |access-date=22 July 2018 |archive-date=2 November 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181102134021/https://offsidefootball.com/arsenal-reach-agreement-over-french-centre-forwards-deal/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

It wasn’t until on 16 September 2018 when Fortuné made his professional debut for Sion against [[FC Lausanne-Sport|Lausanne-Sport]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sion mit Mühe in Lausanne, Aarau weiter sieglos|url=https://www.20min.ch/sport/fussball/story/Sion-mit-Muehe-in-Lausanne--Aarau-weiter-sieglos-31744205|publisher=20 Minutes|language=de|date=16 September 2018|access-date=30 November 2018}}</ref> Six days later, on 22 September 2018, he made his league debut for the club, in a 4–1 loss against [[FC Thun]].<ref>{{cite news|title=GC siegt dank Djuricins Doppelpack|url=https://www.20min.ch/sport/dossier/superleague/story/15072170|publisher=20 Minutes|language=de|date=22 September 2018|access-date=30 November 2018}}</ref> Fortuné scored his first goal during his first professional start on 30 September 2018 for Sion against [[FC Luzern|Luzern]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sion steigert sich zum ersten Sieg unter Yakin|url=https://www.suedostschweiz.ch/sport/fussball/2018-09-30/sion-steigert-sich-zum-ersten-sieg-unter-yakin|publisher=Suedostchweiz|language=de|date=30 September 2018|access-date=30 November 2018}}</ref> After making his debut for the club, he appeared in a number of matches.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sion für schwachen Auftritt bestraft|url=https://www.suedostschweiz.ch/sport/fussball/2018-11-04/sion-fuer-schwachen-auftritt-bestraft|publisher=Suedostchweiz|language=de|date=4 November 2018|access-date=30 November 2018}}</ref> His second goal for the club then came on 11 November 2018, in a 2–1 win over [[FC Zürich]].<ref>{{cite news|title=FC Zürich gibt Spiel in Schlussminuten aus der Hand|url=https://www.suedostschweiz.ch/sport/fussball/2018-11-11/fc-zuerich-gibt-spiel-in-schlussminuten-aus-der-hand|publisher=Suedostchweiz|language=de|date=11 November 2018|access-date=30 November 2018}}</ref>

====Loan to Angers====
In 31 January 2021, he was loaned to French [[Ligue 1]] club [[Angers SCO|Angers]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Angers SCO|Angers]]|url=https://www.fcsion.ch/fr/news/detail/1680/yassin-fortune-prete-au-angers-sco|title=Yassin Fortune prêté au Angers SCO|date=31 January 2021|accessdate=20 October 2021|language=fr}}</ref> He only made one substitute appearance for Angers during the loan.

====Loan to Cholet====
On 10 August 2021, he moved on a new French loan to [[SO Cholet|Cholet]], this time in the third-tier [[Championnat National]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[SO Cholet|Cholet]]|url=https://www.socholet.fr/actualites/yassin-fortune-fc-sion-est-prete-au-so-cholet/|title=YASSIN FORTUNÉ (FC SION) EST PRÊTÉ AU SO CHOLET.|date=10 August 2021|accessdate=20 October 2021|language=fr}}</ref>

====Loan to Polissya====
On 17 January 2024, Fortuné was loaned by [[FC Polissya Zhytomyr|Polissya Zhytomyr]] in Ukraine.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Polissya Zhytomyr|url=https://polissyafc.com/news/oficijno-assin-fortun-novij-gravec-fk-polissa|title=ОФІЦІЙНО: ЯССІН ФОРТЮН — НОВИЙ ГРАВЕЦЬ ФК "ПОЛІССЯ"|trans-title=OFFICIAL: YASSIN FORTUNE IS A NEW PLAYER OF FC POLISSIA|date=17 January 2024|access-date=21 January 2024|language=uk}}</ref>

===Vizela===
On 4 August 2025, Fortuné signed a two-season contract with [[F.C. Vizela|Vizela]] in Portuguese second tier.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=F.C. Vizela|url=https://fcvizela.pt/2025/08/04/yassin-fortune-e-reforco-do-fc-vizela/|title=Yassin Fortuné é reforço do FC Vizela|trans-title=Yassin Fortuné joins FC Vizela|date=4 August 2025|access-date=20 September 2025|language=pt}}</ref>

==International career==
Fortuné is eligible to play for [[France national football team|France]], [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] and [[Haiti national football team|Haiti]].<ref name="Fortuné Eligible"/>

===Youth career===
Fortuné scored 5 goals for [[France national under-16 football team|France U16]]<ref name="Corless"/> in 11 appearances, scoring against [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine U16]] and [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic U16]].<ref>{{cite news|title=LARGE SUCCÈS FACE À LA RÉPUBLIQUE TCHÈQUE (6-0)|url=https://www.fff.fr/actualites/145147-553685-large-succes-face-a-la-republique-tcheque-6-0?themePath=equipes-de-france-1/|publisher=FÉDÉRATION FRANÇAISE DE FOOTBALL|language=fr|date=20 January 2015|access-date=30 November 2018}}<br>{{cite news|title=NOUVELLE VICTOIRE, FACE À L'UKRAINE (3-0)|url=https://www.fff.fr/actualites/145288-553882-nouvelle-victoire-face-a-lukraine-3-0?themePath=equipes-de-france-1/|publisher=FÉDÉRATION FRANÇAISE DE FOOTBALL|language=fr|date=22 January 2015|access-date=30 November 2018}}</ref>

Between September 2015 and May 2016, Fortuné then represented [[France national under-17 football team|France U17]],<ref>[https://www.fff.fr/equipes-de-france/tous-les-joueurs/fiche-joueur/2544592399-yassin-fortune FFF - Yassin Fortune] {{in lang|fr}}</ref> scoring 2 goals in 13 appearances, which were against [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic U17]] and [[Denmark national football team|Denmark U17]].<ref>{{cite news|title=NUL POUR FINIR FACE À LA RÉPUBLIQUE TCHÈQUE (1-1)|url=https://www.fff.fr/actualites/166824-573461-nul-pour-finir-face-a-la-republique-tcheque-1-1?themePath=equipes-de-france-1/|publisher=FÉDÉRATION FRANÇAISE DE FOOTBALL|language=fr|date=17 September 2015|access-date=30 November 2018}}<br>{{cite news|title=SOLIDE VICTOIRE FACE AU DANEMARK|url=https://www.fff.fr/actualites/170916-577884-solide-victoire-face-au-danemark?themePath=equipes-de-france-1/|publisher=FÉDÉRATION FRANÇAISE DE FOOTBALL|language=fr|date=12 February 2016|access-date=30 November 2018}}</ref> He also played three matches during the [[2016 UEFA European Under-17 Championship|UEFA European Under-17 Championship]] tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=NUL FACE AU DANEMARK POUR DÉBUTER (0-0)|url=https://www.fff.fr/actualites/171505-578543-nul-face-au-danemark-pour-debuter-0-0?themePath=equipes-de-france-1/|publisher=FÉDÉRATION FRANÇAISE DE FOOTBALL|language=fr|date=6 May 2016|access-date=30 November 2018}}<br>{{cite news|title=LES BLEUETS ÉLIMINÉS (0-1)|url=https://www.fff.fr/actualites/171532-578570-les-bleuets-elimines-0-1?themePath=equipes-de-france-1/|publisher=FÉDÉRATION FRANÇAISE DE FOOTBALL|language=fr|date=12 May 2016|access-date=30 November 2018}}</ref>

Fortuné then scored 7 goals in 15 appearances for [[France national under-18 football team|France U18]].<ref name="talkSport"/>

